# Use-cases vivem aqui, organizados por subdomínio e feature:
#   src/domain/application/use-cases/<subdomain>/<feature>/<verb>-x-use-case.ts
#   src/domain/application/use-cases/<subdomain>/<feature>/<verb>-x-use-case.spec.ts   ← spec ao lado
#   src/domain/application/use-cases/<subdomain>/<feature>/services/                    ← orquestradores
#   src/domain/application/use-cases/<subdomain>/<feature>/errors/                       ← erros do feature
#
# Padrão (estrito):
#   - Use Case retorna Either<UseCaseError<...>, Result>
#   - método público chama-se sempre `execute`
#   - injeta repos + providers (abstract classes), nunca infra concreta
#   - spec usa in-memory repository + factory makeX (camelCase)
